Subject: Deceiver (Chris Thile album) 
To: Loren
Content:
Deceiver is the fourth solo album by American newgrass mandolinist Chris Thile, released on Sugar Hill in 2004. It features a total of 39 instruments, all played by Thile himself. The instruments played on the album include the mandolin, mandola, bass guitar, electric guitar, violin, and various percussion instruments. In 2005, the album was nominated the Grammy Award for Best Engineered Album, Non-Classical to the album's engineers, Thile and Gary Paczosa. In a 2007 interview, Chris Thile discussed what he musically envisioned for Deceiver: All songs by Chris Thile.
